A CIRCULAR queue wraps around a fixed-size array so enqueue/dequeue reuse freed slots — no shifting.
Great for streaming buffers, job schedulers.
A PRIORITY queue always dequeues the HIGHEST-priority (smallest/largest) item. Implemented with a
